Instructions to install and update PHP settings on wordpress container

Pre reqs: ensure you have docker and its dependencies installed on your Raspbery Pi OS 64bit system. 

#In the same directory as your wordpress-docker-compose.yaml file run the following command

#Run the following command to start the container
#In the same directory as your docker-compose-yaml file, run the following command

docker compose up

#After container is running, Access or ssh into the host system and then go into the directory where you linked the wordpress/conf.d volumes. 
cd /dockerdata/wordpress/conf.d #example

sudo nano uploads.ini #use your favorite text editor to create the file uploads.ini or name it anything with .ini as the file extension. File editiors you can use: Vi, Vim, Nano, etc.

#contents for upload.ini. you can copy and paste these variables. you can change the values as needed. To add missing php modules just add them in using the extention= tag and the name of the extention. example: extention=mysqli

#uploads.ini
file_uploads = On
memory_limit = 4G
upload_max_filesize = 10G
post_max_size = 10G
max_execution_time = 6000
max_input_time = 6000
extension=mysqli

# Ctrl+x
# confirm with 'Y'

#Restart wordpress stack after you save to bring up changes.

#you can run 'docker image ls' to list all docker images. you should be able to see the wordpress and mysql images.

#you can run 'docker ps' to see status of running containers. 

#If you started Compose with 'docker compose up -d', stop your services once you've finished with them: 'docker compose stop'